article.description: — Darian Adams had 27 points as Jacksonville State topped Eastern Kentucky 81-68 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Adams carries Jacksonville St. past E. Kentucky 81-68
article.linkText: Adams carries Jacksonville St. past E. Kentucky 81-68
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- — Darian Adams had 27 points as Jacksonville State topped Eastern Kentucky 81-68 on Wednesday night. Kayne Henry had 15 points for Jacksonville State (19-9, 12-3 Atlantic Sun Conference). Jalen Gibbs added 10 points. Michael Moreno had 23 points for the Colonels (12-17, 4-11). Curt Lewis added 16 points. Devontae Blanton had 13 points. The Gamecocks improve to 2-0 against the Colonels this season. Jacksonville State defeated Eastern Kentucky 76-65 on Jan. 15. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
